The course deals with the grammar of the Estonian language from the point of view of teaching Estonian as a foreign language. Learn to explain and justify the formation and use of grammatical forms. Grammar study materials are created independently.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide future teachers of Estonian as a foreign language with the necessary knowledge and skills to teach Estonian grammar to non-Estonians.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course the students
1) have knowledge of the problems in teaching Estonian Grammar to non-Estonian speakers;
2) can analyse and teach different domains of Estonian Grammar to non-Estonian speakers;
3) can use different materials of teaching Estonian Grammar and create new exercises if necessary
